#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Discover how to create meta-packages known as \"bundles\" in Spack to group "
"multiple packages together for a single installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:13
msgid "Bundle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:15
msgid ""
"``BundlePackage`` represents a set of packages that are expected to work "
"well together, such as a collection of commonly used software libraries. The "
"associated software is specified as dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:18
msgid ""
"If it makes sense, variants, conflicts, and requirements can be added to the "
"package. :ref:`Variants <variants>` ensure that common build options are "
"consistent across the packages supporting them. :ref:`Conflicts "
"<packaging_conflicts>` prevent attempts to build with known bugs and "
"limitations. :ref:`Requirements <packaging_requires>` prevent attempts to "
"build without critical options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:23
msgid ""
"For example, if ``MyBundlePackage`` is known to only build on ``linux``, it "
"could use the ``require`` directive as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:25
msgid ""
"require(\"platform=linux\", msg=\"MyBundlePackage only builds on linux\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:29
msgid "Spack has a number of built-in bundle packages, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:31
msgid ""
"`AmdAocl <https://github.com/spack/spack-packages/blob/develop/repos/"
"spack_repo/builtin/packages/amd_aocl/package.py>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:32
msgid ""
"`EcpProxyApps <https://github.com/spack/spack-packages/blob/develop/repos/"
"spack_repo/builtin/packages/ecp_proxy_apps/package.py>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:33
msgid ""
"`Libc <https://github.com/spack/spack-packages/blob/develop/repos/spack_repo/"
"builtin/packages/libc/package.py>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:34
msgid ""
"`Xsdk <https://github.com/spack/spack-packages/blob/develop/repos/spack_repo/"
"builtin/packages/xsdk/package.py>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:36
msgid ""
"where ``Xsdk`` also inherits from ``CudaPackage`` and ``RocmPackage`` and "
"``Libc`` is a virtual bundle package for the C standard library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:40
msgid "Creation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:42
msgid ""
"Be sure to specify the ``bundle`` template if you are using ``spack create`` "
"to generate a package from the template. For example, use the following "
"command to create a bundle package whose class name will be ``Mybundle``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:45
msgid "$ spack create --template bundle --name mybundle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:52
msgid "Phases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:54
msgid ""
"The ``BundlePackage`` base class does not provide any phases by default "
"since the bundle does not represent a build system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:58
msgid "URL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:60
msgid ""
"The ``url`` property does not have meaning since there is no package-"
"specific code to fetch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:64
msgid "Version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/bundlepackage.rst:66
msgid ""
"At least one ``version`` must be specified in order for the package to build."
msgstr ""
